      "writtenOn": "2021-01-29T07:13:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e we\u0027d see a new timestamp,\nYes, missed that. But why would it result to a new run because of a different timestamp?\n\nSo say \n\n  T1: user1 CQ+2 \n  T2: user2 CQ+2 \n  T3: CQ starts the full run\n  T4: user1 for some reason remove CQ+2 vote\n\nShall we still continue the run if CQ+2 from user 2 is valid (i.e. have full run access)?",
      "parentUuid": "bb50d9ee_3818903d",
      "revId": "96b1a497786a86a9a8b23a5ff6c4481bd0536811",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fcf1bbbc_bfe8d782",
        "filename": "cv/internal/run/impl/cl_update_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 118,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-29T14:58:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "great example, and you are spot on that ACLs may need re-evaluation.\n\nCQD starts a new Run.\nWhile CV can re-use old Run, I think it\u0027s cleaner to create a new Run to avoid thinking about edge cases in ACLs (and cost attribution (some day)).\n\nHowever, user1 doesn\u0027t usually remove CQ+2 vote just for fun. I think it may be even cleaner to remove *all* CQ+2 votes and ask user(s) to decide what they really want. WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "f30d0b4b_a5c34dbb",
      "revId": "96b1a497786a86a9a8b23a5ff6c4481bd0536811",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6483bf42_07420b05",
        "filename": "cv/internal/run/impl/cl_update_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 118,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-29T18:47:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s ideal that the removal of user1 vote can void the vote from user2. Since at the time, the intention to trigger a Run from user 2 remains unchanged. If I think of a different scenario that in the middle of the run, user 1 somehow lose ACL, I think we still want the run to continue(or creating a new run) since there\u0027s still another valid vote to back this run.\n\nSo now, within the options between reusing the same run or creating a new run, I think both of them make sense to me from different perspectives. Since we are talking about a relative rare use case, so I\u0027m actually leaning towards creating a new run now because it is definitely easier to implement. (Also, apart from re-eval ACL, I think CV also need to take care of the per-user quota.)\n\ntl;dr, I\u0027ll add a todo to re-evaluate this after m1.",
      "parentUuid": "fcf1bbbc_bfe8d782",
